{
  "text": "Coccidiosis due to E. caviae is another problem in domestic cavy worldwide [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . A recent study in Italy [CITATION_3] showed an infection rate of 10 %, which is comparable with the rate obtained in this study (14.3 %) . Though the infection rate was low, the infection was severe with greater than 10000 oocysts per gram of feces in a single animal. This might be related to the poor hygienic conditions associated with the husbandry practices of the geographic origin of the animal purchased. Indeed cavies purchased from different sources for use at the TRF are often introduced in the flock without any quarantine period. No overdispersion (k > 1) was observed in the distribution of E. caviae indicating a uniform exposure and/or susceptibility of the animals to the parasite.",
  "citation_candidates": [
